!!!!!!

 `hibernate-validator` is the reference implementation of the Bean Validation API (`jakarta.validation`).
 It is not related to database access—Spring Boot uses it to validate request bodies and method parameters (e.g., in REST controllers) automatically.

 Without `hibernate-validator`, validation annotations like `@NotNull`, `@Size`, and `@DecimalMin` will not be processed, and validation errors will not be triggered for incoming HTTP requests.

 In summary:
 - `hibernate-validator` enables runtime validation for your DTOs, regardless of database usage.
 - It is required for Spring Boot to support `jakarta.validation` annotations.
